r, except for the critical electron\nconcentration of as low as 6% in the latter compound. For the present\nsuperconductor, notably, the existence of hole-type carriers has been indicated\nin the normal state from the Hall effect measurements. The\nSr$_{1-x}$La$_x$FBiS$_2$ system providing the phase diagram for the rigid-band\ndoping in the BiS$_2$ layer would be another prototypical example of\nsuperconductivity derived from a doped layered band insulator, hosting both\nhole-like and electron-like Fermi surfaces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Nov 2013 16:06:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-18"}
